cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on inferring user attributes and interests from user-generated visual content (images) on social networks. This involves analyzing the content of individual images and aggregating the image-level knowledge to infer user-level interest distribution. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image analysis and understanding. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for label propagation and category-level knowledge, which falls under social and information networks (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves predicting user interests and personalization, and natural language processing (cs.CL) as it involves analyzing textual content associated with images.
